{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.26",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 26 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:1",
      "text": "Happy is the husband of a good wife: for the number of his years is double.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:2",
      "text": "A virtuous woman rejoiceth her husband, and shall fulfil the years of his life in peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:3",
      "text": "A good wife is a good portion, she shall be given in the portion of them that fear God, to a man for his good deeds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:4",
      "text": "Rich or poor, if his heart is good, his countenance shall be cheerful at all times.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:5",
      "text": "Of three things my heart hath been afraid, and at the fourth my face hath trembled:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:6",
      "text": "The accusation of a city, and the gathering together of the people:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:7",
      "text": "And a false calumny, all are more grievous than death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:8",
      "text": "A jealous woman is the grief and mourning of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:9",
      "text": "With a jealous woman is a scourge of the tongue which communicateth with all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:10",
      "text": "As a yoke of oxen that is moved to and fro, so also is a wicked woman: he that hath hold of her, is as he that taketh hold of a scorpion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:11",
      "text": "A drunken woman is a great wrath: and her reproach and shame shall not be hid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:12",
      "text": "The fornication of a woman shall be known by the haughtiness of her eyes and by her eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:13",
      "text": "On a daughter that turneth not away herself, set a strict watch: lest finding an opportunity she abuse herself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:14",
      "text": "Take heed of the impudence of her eyes, and wonder not if she slight thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:15",
      "text": "She will open her mouth as a thirsty traveller to the fountain, and will drink of every water near her, and will sit down by every hedge, and open her quiver against every arrow, until she fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:16",
      "text": "The grace of a diligent woman shall delight her husband, and shall fat his bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:17",
      "text": "Her discipline is the gift of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:18",
      "text": "Such is a wise and silent woman, and there is nothing so much worth as a well instructed soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:19",
      "text": "A holy and shamefaced woman is grace upon grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:20",
      "text": "And no price is worthy of a continent soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:21",
      "text": "As the sun when it riseth to the world in the high places of God, so is the beauty of a good wife for the ornament of her house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:22",
      "text": "As the lamp shining upon the holy candlestick, so is the beauty of the face in a ripe age,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:23",
      "text": "As golden pillars upon bases of silver, so are the firm feet upon the soles of a steady woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:24",
      "text": "As everlasting foundations upon a solid rock, so the commandments of God in the heart of a holy woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:25",
      "text": "At two things my heart is grieved, and the third bringeth anger upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:26",
      "text": "A man of war fainting through poverty, and a man of sense despised:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:27",
      "text": "And he that passeth over from justice to sin, God hath prepared such an one for the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.26.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 26:28",
      "text": "Two sorts of callings have appeared to me hard and dangerous: a merchant is hardly free from negligence: and a huckster shall not be justified from the sins of the lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
